Mumias police yesterday gunned down an armed robber at Mwitoti shopping centre.Mumias East subcounty AP commander Ezekiel Ogutu said Idris Mutimba s two accomplices fled. He said police on patrol were alerted about the robbery by a watchman. Police confronted the three and told them to surrender, but they refused to do so, Ogutu said. He said Mutimba s accomplices were at the back of the shop and escaped before police opened fire.Ogutu said Mutimba was a notorious criminal who dropped out of Eluche Primary School. He said Mutimba had earlier attacked a Chinese worker at a construction site near Shianda market.Police recovered a hacksaw used to cut padlocks at the shop s entry. Mutimba said the thugs took advantage of the Manchester versus Liverpool match to rob shops.